<chapter id="chap-Users_Guide-Branding">
	<title>Branding</title>
	<para>
		Publican uses brands to apply a consistent look and style to html and pdf output. Brands are collections of files installed to <filename>/usr/share/publican/Common_Content/<replaceable>brand</replaceable>/</filename>. Publican ships with one brand, <filename>common/</filename>.
	</para>
	<para>
		Brands for JBoss, GIMP, Red Hat Enterprise Linux, Fedora and oVirt can be installed using <command>yum install publican-<replaceable>brand</replaceable></command>.
	</para>
